  "prompt": "How can we check whether a number is prime or not?",
  "response": "To determine whether a number is prime, you can use the following algorithm. This method checks divisibility by any integer up to the square root of the number in question:\n\n1. **Understand Prime Numbers:** A prime number is a natural number greater than 1 with no positive divisors other than 1 and itself.\n\n2. **Basic Checks:**\n   - If the number is less than 2, it is not prime.\n   - If the number is 2 or 3, it is prime (since these are the smallest prime numbers).\n   - If the number is even and greater than 2, it is not prime.\n\n3. **Check for Divisibility:** \n   - For numbers greater than 3, check divisibility starting from 3 to the square root of the number.\n   - You only need to test for factors up to the square root of the number because if `n = a * b`, then one of the factors `a` or `b` must be less than or equal to the square root of `n`.\n\n4. **Iterate with a Stepsize:**\n   - Start checking for factors with 3 and continue with odd numbers (since all even numbers greater than 2 are not prime).\n   - For each odd number `i` from 3 to `\u221an`, check if `n % i == 0`.\n   - If `n` is divisible by any of these numbers, it is not prime.\n\n5. **Conclusion:**\n   - If none of the numbers divide `n`, then `n` is prime.\n\nHere\u2019s a simple Python function to check if a number is prime using this algorithm:\n\n```python\nimport math\n\ndef is_prime(n):\n    if n <= 1:\n        return False\n    if n <= 3:\n        return True\n    if n % 2 == 0:\n        return False\n    \n    sqrt_n = int(math.sqrt(n))\n    for i in range(3, sqrt_n + 1, 2):\n        if n % i == 0:\n            return False\n    return True\n\n# Example usage:\nnumber = 29\nprint(f\"{number} is prime: {is_prime(number)}\")\n```\n\nThis function starts by ruling out any number less than 2 or that is even and greater than 2. It then checks for divisibility using odd numbers up to the square root of `n`, providing an efficient way to validate the primality of the number.",
